![][image1]  
As promised, I redid the cofolding of the orthosteric and allosteric ligand sets from the recent paper by [Nittinger et al.](https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2667318525000121) with Boltz-2. While there were a few improvements, the results still largely remain the same. For more information on this analysis, please see my [previous post](https://patwalters.github.io/Three-Papers-Demonstrating-That-Cofolding-Still-Has-a-Ways-to-Go/).  For a higher resolution version of the figure above, please click [here](https://github.com/PatWalters/datafiles/blob/main/figures/boltz_1_vs_boltz_2_orthosteric_allosteric.pdf).
